{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17641101","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17641101"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T19:22:54+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T19:22:54+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17861"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17861","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17861"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.48,0.38,0.1,0,0.04]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10575"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78573"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10575","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10575"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17861"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63915"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4926"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4940"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"10069"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"24653"},{"type":"contributions","id":"24656"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78573","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/78573"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003ELipoprotein lipase (LPL) is an enzyme that breaks down triglycerides in circulating lipoproteins. This process allows tissues to take up fatty acids for energy production or storage.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following tissues expresses lipoprotein lipase on its endothelial cells?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Liver","Skeletal muscle","Pancreas","Kidney","Lung"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESkeletal muscle\u003C/strong\u003E expresses lipoprotein lipase (LPL) on its endothelial cells. LPL hydrolyses triglycerides in lipoproteins into free fatty acids and glycerol, which can then be used by muscle cells for energy production.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELiver\u003C/strong\u003E does not express LPL. Instead, it uses hepatic lipase for lipid metabolism\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPancreas\u003C/strong\u003E primarily produces digestive enzymes and hormones, and does not express LPL\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EKidney\u003C/strong\u003E focuses on filtration and waste excretion rather than lipid metabolism\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELung\u003C/strong\u003E specialises in gas exchange and does not participate significantly in lipid metabolism\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOther tissues that express LPL include adipose tissue and cardiac muscle, where fatty acids are used for energy production or storage.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Lipoprotein lipase (LPL) is primarily expressed in adipose tissue, cardiac muscle, and skeletal muscle where it hydrolyses triglycerides from lipoproteins.","LPL enables uptake of fatty acids into tissues for energy production or storage.","The liver uses hepatic lipase rather than LPL for lipid metabolism."],"references":["Bender, D. A., \u0026 Cunningham, S. M. (2021). Introduction to nutrition and metabolism. CRC Press","Salway, J. G. (2016). Metabolism at a Glance. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Chandel NS. Lipid Metabolism. Cold Spring Harb Perspect Biol. 2021 Sep 1;13(9):a040576. doi: 10.1101/cshperspect.a040576. PMID: 34470787; PMCID: PMC8411952","Wakil SJ, Abu-Elheiga LA. Fatty acid metabolism: target for metabolic syndrome. J Lipid Res. 2009 Apr;50 Suppl(Suppl):S138-43. doi: 10.1194/jlr.R800079-JLR200. Epub 2008 Dec 1. PMID: 19047759; PMCID: PMC2674721"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63915"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17861"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63915","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/63915"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-11T15:35:26+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-11T15:43:06+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10575"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78573"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"4926","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4926"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udec0","name":"Cardiovascular","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":"2024-10-17T23:14:59+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-10-31T09:50:20+10:30"},"relatio